2.Create a table STUDENT have the fields(roll_no, name, age, address, 
gender)and add following constraints on it. 
 
 
               Roll_no – Primary key 
               Name – does not allow null values 
               Age- must be in between (0-99), does not allow null values 
               Gender- default value is ‘m’ 
 
 mysql> create  table student(roll_no int not null primary key,name varchar(50)not null,age int not null,check (age between 0 and 99),address varchar(100),gender char(1) default 'm');
